{"by":"blizow","id":47780004,"parent":47779869,"text":"Cool project. Will have to check it out. Disposable addresses work. They are also a symptom of an inbox that was never designed to survive what we did to it.<p>The defensive infrastructure keeps chasing the offense, but the academic literature predicted this exact dynamic: better filters increase aggregate send volume because senders compensate for filtering losses by sending more.<p>There is a longer argument here about externalities and what the inbox looks like in the future which I just wrote about here if you&#x27;re interested: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;docs.google.com&#x2F;document&#x2F;d&#x2F;1jaogzeZuYetB0z9yNiSqOPTL5Y454l1gXQmDU21qWaU&#x2F;edit?usp=sharing\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;docs.google.com&#x2F;document&#x2F;d&#x2F;1jaogzeZuYetB0z9yNiSqOPTL...</a>","time":1776265095,"type":"comment"}